"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456633","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-08","<p>The Treasury’s sickness absence data for ‘Mental and Behavioural Disorders’ includes stress related conditions.</p><p> </p><p>Details relating to Mental and Behavioural Disorders for the four financial years to March 2015 and the most current information to September 2015 is as follows:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year/period</p></td><td><p>Number of officials</p></td><td><p>Proportion of staff</p></td><td><p>Proportion of total sick leave of the department</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>October 2014 to September 2015</p></td><td><p>38</p></td><td><p>3.1%</p></td><td><p>26%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2014 to March 2015</p></td><td><p>36</p></td><td><p>3.2%</p></td><td><p>25%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2013 to March 2014</p></td><td><p>33</p></td><td><p>3.0%</p></td><td><p>25%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2012 to March 2013</p></td><td><p>32</p></td><td><p>2.8%</p></td><td><p>19%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2011 to March 2012</p></td><td><p>28</p></td><td><p>2.4%</p></td><td><p>18%</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456633/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-08T14:29:07.08Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456633/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456633/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-01","Treasury: Sick Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many officials of his Department took sick leave for reasons relating to stress in each of the last five years; and what proportion of (a) his Department's staff and (b) total sick leave the sick leave of such officials represented in each such year.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","29109"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456634","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-08","<p>A total of 85 officials resigned from the department during the last 12 months in which records are available, from February 2015 until January 2016.</p><p>The number of resignations for each of the 12 months can be viewed in the table below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Month</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Resignation</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Feb-15</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mar-15</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr-15</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>May-15</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jun-15</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jul-15</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Aug-15</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Sep-15</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct-15</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Nov-15</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Dec-15</p></td><td><p>8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan-16</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Grand Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>85</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456634/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-08T14:26:25.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456634/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456634/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-01","Treasury: Resignations","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many of his Department's officials resigned in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","29054"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456635","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-04","<p>DWP has succeeded in reducing sickness absence from an annual average of 11.1 days per employee in 2007 to 6.18 days per employee currently. This is one of the lowest rates across the public sector.</p><p> </p><p>Our Attendance Management policy is supportive and we are committed to helping our people maintain good health. DWP is committed to improving mental ill health, including stress.</p><p> </p><p>We support employees through access to comprehensive stress risk assessments, Occupational Health services, and our Employee Assistance Programme. DWP is currently introducing Mental Health First Aid to further add to the support available.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The number of employees with a sickness absence reason of ‘stress’ over the last 5 years is shown below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Number of employees with sickness absence recorded as ‘Stress’</p></td><td><p>Number of employees with sickness absence reason recorded as ‘stress’ as % of end of year headcount*</p></td><td><p>Number of working days lost recorded as ‘stress’ as % of all working days lost due to sickness absence</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan-Dec 15</p></td><td><p>2,581</p></td><td><p>3.01%</p></td><td><p>10.57%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan-Dec 14</p></td><td><p>2,886</p></td><td><p>3.15%</p></td><td><p>11.06%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan-Dec 13</p></td><td><p>3,401</p></td><td><p>3.38%</p></td><td><p>11.15%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan-Dec 12</p></td><td><p>3,313</p></td><td><p>3.07%</p></td><td><p>9.63%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan-Dec 11</p></td><td><p>3,288</p></td><td><p>3.20%</p></td><td><p>9.26%</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456635/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-04T13:33:59.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456635/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456635/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-01","Department for Work and Pensions: Sick Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many officials of his Department took sick leave for reasons relating to stress in each of the last five years; and what proportion of (a) his Department's staff and (b) total sick leave the sick leave of such officials represented in each such year.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","29117"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456636","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-04","<p>The numbers of employees who resigned from the Department for Work and Pensions in each of the last 12 months is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Month</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Resignations</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Resignations as a % of workforce</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>February 2015</p></td><td><p>121</p></td><td><p>0.13%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>March 2015</p></td><td><p>156</p></td><td><p>0.17%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April 2015</p></td><td><p>177</p></td><td><p>0.19%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>May 2015</p></td><td><p>186</p></td><td><p>0.20%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>June 2015</p></td><td><p>151</p></td><td><p>0.16%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>July 2015</p></td><td><p>219</p></td><td><p>0.25%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>August 2015</p></td><td><p>212</p></td><td><p>0.24%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>September 2015</p></td><td><p>233</p></td><td><p>0.27%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>October 2015</p></td><td><p>175</p></td><td><p>0.20%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>November 2015</p></td><td><p>171</p></td><td><p>0.20%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>December 2015</p></td><td><p>136</p></td><td><p>0.16%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January 2016</p></td><td><p>134</p></td><td><p>0.16%</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456636/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-04T13:39:47.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456636/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456636/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-03-01","Department for Work and Pensions: Resignations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many officials of his Department resigned in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","29118"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456637","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-09","<p>The information requested is not available in this format.</p><p> </p><p>HM Revenue and Customs publishes estimates of the tax gap each year. The latest edition was published on 22 October 2015.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/measuring-tax-gaps" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/measuring-tax-gaps</a></p><p> </p><p>Estimates are made for all major taxes, including corporation tax and income tax. However, this information is not broken down in such a way that can be used to identify the loss of tax receipts due to the tax regimes requested.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456637/answer",,,,,"29332 ; 29333 ; 29334 ; 29335 ; 29337 ; 29338","2016-03-09T11:12:37.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456637/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456637/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-03-01","Taxation: Crown Dependencies and British Overseas Territories","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate the Government has made of the effect of tax regimes in each Crown Dependency and Overseas Territory on UK tax receipts from individuals.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","29336"
