lpline for the financial year 2016-17. Polaris, a US-based Non-Governmental Organisation (NGO), is establishing an enhanced UK helpline in collaboration with a UK-based NGO, which will supersede the current NSPCC helpline. The NSPCC helpline will remain in operation until the enhanced helpline is up and running. Start up funding of up to £1 million has been provided by Google.org. The new helpline is expected to be in operation later this year.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456703/answer",,,,,"29220 ; 29222","2016-03-14T15:14:04.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456703/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456703/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-03-01","Slavery","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, for what reasons the Government no longer funds the NSPCC helpline on modern slavery; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Fiona Mactaggart","Slough","Fiona Mactaggart","29221"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456704","Department of Health","false","2016-03-08","<p>NHS England has advised that all patients diagnosed with colorectal cancer will continue to be able to access treatment for their disease. It is not possible to estimate the numbers of patients who will be able to access both current and future specific treatments for colorectal cancers as there is a wide range of treatments available and these are ever changing.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456704/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-08T11:40:40.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456704/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456704/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-01","Bowel Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate his Department has made of the number of patients who will be able to access treatments for colorectal cancer on the NHS from April 2016.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","29306"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456705","Department of Health","false","2016-03-08","<p>My Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Health has been kept informed as this work has been progressed.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised that it envisages, under the new arrangements for the Cancer Drugs Fund, that a greater number of cancer drugs will be funded from baseline commissioning. This will be as a consequence of more appropriate pricing arrangements proposed by pharmaceutical manufacturers and better evidence being available through the Fund as to longer term patient outcomes.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456705/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-08T11:34:06.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456705/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456705/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-01","Cancer: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent discussions he has had with NHS England and NICE on the Cancer Drugs Fund consultation; and whether he discussed with those bodies whether proposals on the future of that fund would (a) increase and (b) restrict access to cancer medicines.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","29210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456706","Department of Health","false","2016-03-08","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 24 February 2016 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=27585" target="_blank">27585</a>.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456706/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-08T11:41:51.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456706/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456706/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-03-01","Bowel Cancer: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions his Department has had with NICE and NHS England on the availability of Erbitux for metastatic colorectal cancer patients.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","29211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456707","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-03-04","<p>It is already best practice for vets, re-homing centres and dog wardens to scan strays and they have a duty of care to do so. To assist dog wardens, the Kennel Club has provided free scanners to all local authorities. We will also be reminding these parties of the need to scan dogs.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456707/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-04T13:44:10.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456707/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456707/answer",,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-03-01","Dogs: Tagging","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will take steps to encourage vets, re-homing centres and dog wardens to scan stray dogs for microchips.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","29081"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456708","Department for International Development","false","2016-03-07","<p>Kashmir benefits from national programmes in Pakistan and India to promote economic growth and improve education and health services across each country.</p><p>DFID does not routinely measure total expenditure directed to sub-national geographies outside our focal states or provinces. We focus our work on the states of India and provinces of Pakistan where we can have the largest impact and where the need is greatest. Currently, these areas do not include Kashmir.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456708/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-07T15:16:21.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456708/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456708/answer",,,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-03-01","Kashmir: Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what projects her Department sponsors in Kashmir; and how much her Department spent in Kashmir since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","29320"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456709","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-09","<p>The Department does not hold data on such convictions.</p><p>The Housing and Planning Bill contains measures to tackle rogue landlords who rent out sub-standard accommodation. Proposals include a database of rogue landlords and property agents, introducing banning orders for serious or repeat offenders, a tougher fit and proper person test, extending Rent Repayment Orders and introducing civil penalties of up to £30,000.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456709/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-09T16:54:07.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456709/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456709/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-01","Housing Act 2004: Convictions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many convictions resulted from offences under (a) Part 1 and (b) Part 2 of the Housing Act 2004 in (i) England and (ii) each local justice area in (A) 2013, (B) 2014 and (C) 2015.","false","Biography information for Ms Karen Buck","Westminster North","Ms Karen Buck","29353"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456710","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-09","<p>The Department does not collect this data. It is the responsibility of local authorities to decide appropriate staffing levels to meet their obligations on enforcement.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456710/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-09T16:58:15.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456710/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456710/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-01","Housing Act 2004","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many (a) environmental health officers and (b) other staff in local authorities were responsible for enforcement of provisions in the Housing Act 2004 in (i) 2012-13, (ii) 2013-14 and (iii) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Ms Karen Buck","Westminster North","Ms Karen Buck","29354"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456711","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-03-04","<p>The English Housing Survey, funded by the Department, published its Headline Report 2014-15 in February 2016 which showed that 27% of privately rented households are in receipt of housing benefit.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456711/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-04T14:01:03.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456711/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456711/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-03-01","Private Rented Housing: Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what research his Department has conducted on the willingness of landlords to let properties to tenants in receipt of housing benefit; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ms Karen Buck","Westminster North","Ms Karen Buck","29261"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456712","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-03-04","<p>HMCTS does not collect data to the level of detail required to identify local authorities or social service authorities, or applications in respect of the Children Act 2004. The information can only be collated at disproportionate cost.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456712/answer",,,,,"29262 ; 29263 ; 29265","2016-03-04T12:28:24.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456712/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/456712/answer",,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-03-01","Judicial Review: Social Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many applications for judicial review have been (a) made and (b) successful in each social services authority in England in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Ms Karen Buck","Westminster North","Ms Karen Buck","29264"
