ncreased from a total of 56,250 in 2010 who were recorded as having a primary need of autism, but it is not directly comparable to the 2015 figures because of a change in collection methodology.</p><p> </p><p>New statutory guidance was issued in England in March 2015 to support implementation of the Adult Autism Strategy. This set out what people seeking an autism diagnosis can expect from local authorities and NHS bodies. The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence has published three clinical guidelines on autism and a quality standard to assist health managers and practitioners in developing services. This includes a recommendation that an assessment is started within three months of the referral. NHS England has commenced a programme to visit CCGs to identify and share good practice in accessing autism diagnosis, and look at possible barriers. NHS England will complete a report on this by the end of April 2016.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455946/answer",,,,,"HL6523 ; HL6524","2016-03-14T14:03:59.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455946/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455946/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-29","Autism","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether health managers and practitioners in England have had access to the 2008 Department of Health, Social Services and Public Safety Independent Review of Autism Services or to any similar independent guidance regarding appropriate timescale targets for moving from initial autism referrals to diagnosis and appropriate care.","false","Biography information for Lord Maginnis of Drumglass",,"Lord Maginnis of Drumglass","HL6526"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455947","Home Office","false","2016-03-03","<p>This information is not collected centrally.</p>",,"Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455947/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-03T14:56:52.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455947/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455947/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-02-29","Dangerous Dogs","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many seized dogs are being held by police services across the UK, and how many of those have been held for over one year.","false","Biography information for Baroness Parminter",,"Baroness Parminter","HL6527"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455948","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-14","<p>The Electoral Commission published its “UK Parliamentary General Election 2015: Campaign spending report” on 29 February 2016. The Government is considering the report and will respond in due course.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455948/answer",,,,,"HL6529 ; HL6530 ; HL6531","2016-03-14T17:56:20.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455948/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455948/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-29","Elections: Expenditure","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their response to the Electoral Commission’s conclusion in its report <i>UK Parliamentary General Election 2015: Campaign spending report</i>, that the "Commission should be provided with investigative powers and sanctions for offences relating to candidate spending and donations at specified elections"<i>.</i>","false","Biography information for Lord Rennard",,"Lord Rennard","HL6528"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455949","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-14","<p>The Electoral Commission published its “UK Parliamentary General Election 2015: Campaign spending report” on 29 February 2016. The Government is considering the report and will respond in due course.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455949/answer",,,,,"HL6528 ; HL6530 ; HL6531","2016-03-14T17:56:20.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455949/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455949/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-29","Elections: Expenditure","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their response to the Electoral Commission’s conclusion in its report <i>UK Parliamentary General Election 2015: Campaign spending report</i>, that "in principle, staff costs associated with regulated campaign spending should be included within the regulatory controls for all types of campaigners: candidates, political parties and non-party campaigners".","false","Biography information for Lord Rennard",,"Lord Rennard","HL6529"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455950","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-14","<p>The Electoral Commission published its “UK Parliamentary General Election 2015: Campaign spending report” on 29 February 2016. The Government is considering the report and will respond in due course.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455950/answer",,,,,"HL6528 ; HL6529 ; HL6531","2016-03-14T17:56:20.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455950/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455950/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-29","Elections: Expenditure","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their response to the Electoral Commission’s conclusion in its report <i>UK Parliamentary General Election 2015: Campaign spending report</i>, that "there is a case for reviewing and increasing the present cap of £20,000 on our power to issue sanctions".","false","Biography information for Lord Rennard",,"Lord Rennard","HL6530"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455951","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-14","<p>The Electoral Commission published its “UK Parliamentary General Election 2015: Campaign spending report” on 29 February 2016. The Government is considering the report and will respond in due course.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455951/answer",,,,,"HL6528 ; HL6529 ; HL6530","2016-03-14T17:56:20.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455951/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455951/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-29","Elections: Expenditure","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their response to the Electoral Commission’s <i>UK Parliamentary General Election 2015: Campaign spending report</i>.","false","Biography information for Lord Rennard",,"Lord Rennard","HL6531"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455952","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-14","<p>The Government is currently considering the recommendations made by the Law Commissions in their interim report of 4 February. This is a wide-ranging report that covers a number of complex issues and it is important that the Government give the report due consideration before a formal response is made.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455952/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-14T17:56:34.083Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455952/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455952/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-29","Elections","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their response the Law Commissions’ recommendations to reform UK electoral law.","false","Biography information for Lord Rennard",,"Lord Rennard","HL6532"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455953","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-10","<p>Sir Eric Pickles will make his recommendations as soon as he is able. 66 written submissions are under consideration, as well as evidence provided in meetings with specific people and at a seminar of academics, stakeholder organisations and political parties.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455953/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-10T15:25:19.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455953/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455953/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-29","Electoral Fraud Review","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they will publish details of the recommendations for potential changes to electoral legislation by Sir Eric Pickles MP.","false","Biography information for Lord Rennard",,"Lord Rennard","HL6533"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455954","Home Office","false","2016-03-07","<p>The Government is clear that allegations of child abuse should be thoroughly and properly investigated. However decisions about arrest and charge are an operational matter for the police and Crown Prosecution Service and it would be inappropriate for the Home Office to comment further.</p>",,"Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455954/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-07T17:54:02.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455954/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455954/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-02-29","Offences against Children","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their assessment of Detective Superintendent McDonald's description of child abuse allegations against Sir Edward Heath, Lord Bramall and Lord Brittan as "credible and true", and whether they have made representations to the Metropolitan Police Service that an apology should be issued regarding that statement.","false","Biography information for Lord Renwick of Clifton",,"Lord Renwick of Clifton","HL6534"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455955","Home Office","false","2016-03-07","<p>The Home Office does not employ Immigration Officers to assess asylum claims. Staff employed to make asylum decisions are either Executive Officers or Higher Executive Officers with a minimum educational requirement of 2 GCE A Level passes A-C and 5 GCSE passes including Mathematics and English.</p>",,"Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455955/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-07T17:28:51.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455955/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455955/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-02-29","Asylum","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what qualifications are required for Immigration Officers who decide the success or failure of asylum applications.","false","Biography information for Lord Roberts of Llandudno",,"Lord Roberts of Llandudno","HL6535"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455956","Home Office","false","2016-03-07","<p>Figures on asylum appeal determinations are published quarterly by the Home Office in the Immigration Statistics release. The following table gives annual figures for asylum appeals that were allowed, from 2011 to 2015.</p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="4"><p><strong>Asylum appeals allowed, from 2011 to 2015</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Appeals Allowed</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2,779</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2,208</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2,078</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>1,758</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>3,234</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="11"><p><strong>Source: Table as_14, volume 4 of Asylum data tables, <em>Immigration Statistics</em> October to December 2015, Home Office</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>A copy of the latest release, Immigration Statistics October to December 2015, is available from https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/immigration-statistics-october-to-december-2015</p>",,"Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455956/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-07T17:28:28.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455956/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455956/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-02-29","Asylum: Appeals","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many initial asylum application decisions have been overturned on appeal in the past five years.","false","Biography information for Lord Roberts of Llandudno",,"Lord Roberts of Llandudno","HL6536"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455957","Home Office","false","2016-03-07","<p>The table provided gives annual figures for the number of appeals allowed from applicants aged between 18 and 25 at the time of applying for asylum. This is a subset of published data.</p><p><strong>Asylum appeals allowed, for applicants aged 18 to 25 at the time of asylum application, 2011 to 2015</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Appeals allowed, age 18 to 25 (1)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>804</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>622</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>549</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>476</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>949</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Source: Home Office, subset of published appeals allowed figures in table as_14, volume 4 of the Asylum data tables, Immigration Statistics October to December 2015</p><p>(1) Age relates to the age at initial asylum application</p><p>A copy of the latest release, Immigration Statistics October to December 2015, is available from https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/immigration-statistics-october-to-december-2015.</p>",,"Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455957/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-07T17:27:41.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455957/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455957/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-02-29","Asylum: Appeals","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many asylum applications by those aged 18 to 25 have been overturned on appeal in the past five years.","false","Biography information for Lord Roberts of Llandudno",,"Lord Roberts of Llandudno","HL6537"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455958","Department for International Development","false","2016-03-14","<p>Since the start of the Mediterranean migration crisis, the Department for International Development has provided £55 million in response, including over £19 million in Greece. Assistance through the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees and non-governmental organisations has provided life-saving aid to migrants and refugees to support reception, protection, accommodation, and meet basic needs. We are monitoring the situation closely. We stand ready to meet additional priority needs and are sending a team to Greece to assess the situation.</p>",,"Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455958/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-14T16:40:57.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455958/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455958/answer",,,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-02-29","Immigration: Greece","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what aid has been given to Greece to assist that country in supporting migrants and refugees.","false","Biography information for Lord Roberts of Llandudno",,"Lord Roberts of Llandudno","HL6538"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455959","Home Office","false","2016-03-07","<p>The Government is working closely with local authorities, international delivery partners and the voluntary sector, putting in place the plans and structures to deliver this and ensuring the system is scaled up in a way that protects the interests of all concerned. The number resettled in a particular period will depend on a range of factors. This includes the number of referrals we have received from the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees and the number of confirmed places we have received from local authorities that are suitable for the specific needs of those who have been accepted for resettlement. Progress on resettlement will be indicated in quarterly immigration statistics - the last set were published in February 2016 and showed 1,085 people resettled between October and December 2015.</p><p>The Government remains on track to resettle 20,000 refugees by the end of the Parliament.</p>",,"Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455959/answer",,,,,"HL6540","2016-03-07T17:49:04.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455959/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455959/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-02-29","Refugees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what proportion of the 20,000 refugees promised to be accepted in the UK will have arrived by May.","false","Biography information for Lord Roberts of Llandudno",,"Lord Roberts of Llandudno","HL6539"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455960","Home Office","false","2016-03-07","<p>The Government is working closely with local authorities, international delivery partners and the voluntary sector, putting in place the plans and structures to deliver this and ensuring the system is scaled up in a way that protects the interests of all concerned. The number resettled in a particular period will depend on a range of factors. This includes the number of referrals we have received from the United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees and the number of confirmed places we have received from local authorities that are suitable for the specific needs of those who have been accepted for resettlement. Progress on resettlement will be indicated in quarterly immigration statistics - the last set were published in February 2016 and showed 1,085 people resettled between October and December 2015.</p><p>The Government remains on track to resettle 20,000 refugees by the end of the Parliament.</p>",,"Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455960/answer",,,,,"HL6539","2016-03-07T17:49:04.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455960/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455960/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-02-29","Refugees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what timetable is proposed to ensure that their promise to welcome 20,000 refugees by 2020 is fulfilled.","false","Biography information for Lord Roberts of Llandudno",,"Lord Roberts of Llandudno","HL6540"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455961","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-16","<p>1,900 additional staff across the three intelligence agencies will be recruited over the Spending Review period to 2020. Specific pay and reward details cannot be disclosed for national security reasons however pay and reward packages for staff at the intelligence agencies are under regular review to ensure that what can be offered reflects both the unique challenges the agencies face, and the high level of ability and skill required to meet them.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455961/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-16T17:26:51.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455961/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455961/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-29","Intelligence Services: Recruitment","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is the timetable for the recruitment of the 1,900 additional intelligence personnel announced in November 2015, and what is being done to ensure that the salary package offered attracts sufficiently talented applicants.","false","Biography information for Lord Strasburger",,"Lord Strasburger","HL6541"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455962","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-07","<p>While we have not made any representations to the Israeli authorities on this specific issue, we consistently urge Israeli contacts against the use of excessive force.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455962/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-07T16:02:49.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455962/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455962/answer",,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-29","Israel: Palestinians","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel regarding the use of tear gas at Qitoun checkpoint against Palestinian children on their way to school.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL6542"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455963","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-07","<p>On 18 February during his visit to Israel, the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my hon. Friend the Member for Bournemouth East (Mr Ellwood), expressed his disappointment to Israel’s Deputy Foreign Minister at Israel's unwillingness to facilitate meetings for the British lawyers. We are now considering alternative means to take forward this work.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455963/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-07T16:03:07.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455963/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455963/answer",,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-29","Israel: Palestinians","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what action they intend to take following the second postponement of the visit to follow up the June 2012 report <i>Children in Military Custody</i>.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL6543"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455964","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-07","<p>The centenary of the Balfour Declaration in 2017 is one of a number of significant upcoming anniversaries relating to the Middle East. We are beginning to plan for these anniversaries in conjunction with our international partners. These plans are still at an early stage.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455964/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-07T16:11:47.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455964/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455964/answer",,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-29","Israel: Palestinians","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what plans they have to commemorate the centenary of the Balfour Declaration.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL6544"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455965","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-07","<p>We are in the early stages of consultation with the French and other partners on this potential proposal, and will assess how the UK should participate on the basis of whether or not it supports progress towards a two-state solution.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455965/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-07T16:12:01.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455965/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455965/answer",,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-29","Israel: Palestinians","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what involvement they intend to have in the French-organised Israel-Palestine conference planned for this summer.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL6545"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455966","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-07","We will continue to raise our objections to settlements with the Israeli government. On 18 February during his visit to Israel, the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my hon. Friend the Member for Bournemouth East (Mr Ellwood), discussed the issue of settlement with Israeli Prime Minister, Benjamin Netanyahu, reiterating the UK's position.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455966/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-07T16:12:19.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455966/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455966/answer",,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-29","Israel: Palestinians","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what action the Prime Minister intends to take regarding the continued construction of the illegal settlements in the West Bank following his comments that those settlements are "genuinely shocking" and an "infringement into Palestinian lives and land".","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL6546"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455967","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-07","<p>Whilst we have not raised this particular demolition with the Israeli authorities, our position is clear: demolitions cause unnecessary suffering to ordinary Palestinians and are, in all but the most exceptional of cases, contrary to international humanitarian law. We regularly raise the issue of demolitions with our Israeli counterparts.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455967/answer",,,,,,"2016-03-07T16:12:33.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455967/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455967/answer",,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-29","Israel: Palestinians","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what action they intend to take following the demolition by Israel of the only school in the Abu al-Nuwaar community near the town of al-Eizariya in the occupied West Bank.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL6547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455968","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-09","<p>The tariffs applied by the EU on goods manufactured by China will vary according to the precise product being imported. The EU’s tariff schedule contains in excess of 9000 separate tariff lines on which separate duties are imposed. The table below shows the average Most Favoured Nation (MFN) tariffs imposed by the EU on imports from China for broad product groups. However, in addition to MFN tariffs, additional tariffs may apply to some specific products if anti-dumping or anti subsidy measures are in place.</p><p> </p><p>Further details on the tariffs which apply to specific products can be found at the gov.uk website <a href="https://www.gov.uk/trade-tariff" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/trade-tariff</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Over 200 EU tariffs applied to imports of certain information technology goods and some medical equipment will be eliminated as a result of the successful conclusion in December 2015 of negotiations to expand the Information Technology Agreement.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="3"><p><strong>European Union Most Favoured Nation Tariffs on Imports from non-EU Countries, by Broad Category, Expressed in Percentage Terms </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Product Group</strong></p></td><td colspan="3"><p><strong>Import Duty Expressed </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>in percentage terms</strong></p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Dairy products</p></td><td><p>42.1</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Sugars and confectionery</p></td><td><p>25.2</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Beverages &amp; tobacco</p></td><td><p>20.7</p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> <